The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
		 Wednesday, August 25, 2004  BRIEFS
				 																																	Midnapore, Aug. 24: Mayor Subrata Mukherjee of the Trinamul Congress and five others today surrendered before the Contai sub-divisional judicial magistrate in connection with a 25-year-old case of rioting. They were released on personal bond of Rs 1,000 each. 				 																																	Mukherjee and 28 others had been charged with non-bailable offences, including blocking the convoy of then Prime Minister Morarji Desai. In 1979, Mukherjee, then in the Youth Congress, had called a bandh to protest the arrest of Indira Gandhi.				 																																	Krishnagar: A cache of sophisticated arms and a huge quantity of cough syrup were seized from the India-Bangladesh border at Sikarpur village in Nadia district, about 190 km from Calcutta. Two persons were arrested. 				 																																	Burdwan: Nikhil Das, postmaster of Sakrai village sub-post office, allegedly fled with Rs 10 lakh after an inquiry into a fraud ended on Tuesday. He has been suspended.
